# The relational data tier

Almost every app needs a **relational database** — the durable, transactional **system of record**. Run it yourself on EC2, or hand it to AWS. This module = the **three services** of the data tier.

## RDS — managed relational

Bring schema + queries; AWS runs OS, engine, **patching, backups, failover**.

## Aurora — AWS's own engine

Speaks **MySQL / PostgreSQL** wire, but **rebuilt storage + replication** → higher ceiling, better HA.

## ElastiCache — in-memory cache

Redis / Valkey / Memcached **in front of** the DB → millisecond queries become **microsecond** hits.

**They stack** — durable DB + connection pool + cache on the read path.
